fields.name: Ancestor
fields.description: An animal that is the combination of all, however refuses to leave the comfort of it's cellular state.

fields.name: Aperture
fields.description: Many openings, many views. How would you like to perceive the world?

fields.name: Big Mouth
fields.description: So many words but so little said. Ellipses in thought leave you to wonder if it was worth saying at all.

fields.name: Big Nose
fields.description: Perhaps a bit rude, but this animal knows when something smells fishy. Red and amber fur as fluffy as the truffula tree.

fields.name: Could be a candle, maybe?
fields.description: Maybe its a candle. Maybe that's smoke behind. Or maybe its not a candle. And maybe those are clouds behind.

fields.name: Cute and fluffy
fields.description: Just a fluffy little egg shaped animal. Don't you just want to cuddle up with it?

fields.name: Dinner time
fields.description: This fox looking creature is looking at you like you're a meal. Perhaps you should start running, or not, if you think you can survive.

fields.name: Doctor
fields.description: You are sick. You need help. The doctor will see you now.

fields.name: Doorway to heaven
fields.description: The place everyone hopes they'll end up, yet so few do. Go ahead, say hello to God.

fields.name: Doorway to hell
fields.description: The place everyone hopes they wont end up, yet so many do. Go ahead, say hello to God.

fields.name: Eyes
fields.description: Always watching. This one denotes a red and green theme and is a little spooky.

fields.name: He dropped his banana
fields.description: A funny little black and white picture of a man who seems to have dropped his banana and a single grape. The silhouette is missing hands and appears to have been shot multiple times in the legs. Weird.

fields.name: Here there be monsters
fields.description: Another door aestetic. Less inviting but looks somewhat like the famous door from a certain film franchise. Blue tones and a dark background to contrast the known, and the unknown.

fields.name: Infinity
fields.description: Spirals of infinity, colliding in the middle in a burst of light. Perhaps waves of somekind, who's to say. Slightly off black and white so not completely devoid of life.

fields.name: Just step through
fields.description: Not all doors should be walked through. This one is enticing however. A dark, spooky, scary archway is before you. Is that somthing on the other side?

fields.name: Lakeside
fields.description: Bob Ross style landscape of a lovely lakeside on a sunny day. Walm and calm tones in this one.

fields.name: Mirage
fields.description: Digital rendition of the mirage effect. Strange futuristic red and green colors here. Waves on the ground with an island in the center - and a pyramid.

fields.name: Morning fog
fields.description: Another Bob Ross style water-front painting. Very calm blues in both the water and the sky with the look of an early morning fog or mist rolling in over the surface.

fields.name: Path to enlightenment
fields.description: A carved, sandstone floor leads you to an open door, pouring light in. This is an ancient place, but what lies beyond is older than time.

fields.name: Pondering existence
fields.description: This animal looks out beyond the canvas. It gazes on, and thinks. The browns of its fur give it an ancient look. Perhaps he's been here for some time.

fields.name: Portal to the void
fields.description: If creation came before, this is the end. A black hole into the abyss, devoid of time, end of the road. Dark blues and purples lead to the portal. Is there anything on the other side? Only one way to find out.

fields.name: Proud and noble
fields.description: This creature is a proud one. Look how she stands. A true queen. Fur freshly straightened, but could never lose that natural wave.

fields.name: Puppeteering
fields.description: One holds the other. They share the same design yet they are not the same. Does one control the other. Or do they both control each other.

fields.name: Reflections
fields.description: Simple tres reflected in the water. Natural blues and greens create the effect of still water complimenting the forest.

fields.name: Sanity
fields.description: Its a fragile thing. The constant feeling of being in spotlight and grey your world and make you feel like you're losing your mind.

fields.name: Self thought
fields.description: Thinking about your thinking can really help you change your thinking. Too much will make you selfish. Sometimes our inner world is more colorful than the one outside.

fields.name: Strike a pose
fields.description: Vogue

fields.name: The sands of time
fields.description: The sands of time are often depicted as existing in the hourglass. But that's not true. They flow amogst all things, and exist as their own infinity. This aesthetic works well with any existing decoration you may have.

fields.name: The void
fields.description: Through the door leads you to the thing itself. Dark and wavey, nothing here but shape. Abstract design, it almost looks like the prisoners cinema.

fields.name: Thick skulled
fields.description: This ones a little scary. Some shapeless creature with only a skull set in a dark room. Maybe don't offend this one.

fields.name: Think about it
fields.description: An incredibly accurate despiction of an X-Ray, taken straight from the hospital. With permission of course.

fields.name: Thoughts escape her
fields.description: You know that feeling when you lose your train of thought?

fields.name: Unaware
fields.description: This one reminds me of those old adverts for road safety. Anyway, a fluffy hedgehog doesn't quite see you. A pop of color to fit into anyones aesthetic.

fields.name: What can you see?
fields.description: Oh look, someone'a coming over. Who do you think it is? It's a dark shadow for sure. A little spooky but I'm sure it'll be fine.

fields.name: What's on the other side?
fields.description: A door that appears out of no where can only really be a good thing. This one is even offering you a helping hand. Let's get out of this desert, yeah? Take it's hand.
